The river

A small river
  winds its way
    through the woods;  
it knits journeys,
      divided here
      by the rocks,  
while the current’s song
    calls me out.
    Still, the leaves,
fir trees pull me in –
    I take this refrain
as deep as truth.


- Marianne Moore
